<%- include ('./partials/header-content') -%>
<main>
  <article>
    <section class="section-lvl1">
      <h2>Creating a New User</h2>
      <p><a href="/api/user/new" target="_self">Create a new user</a> to get a unique user ID that can be used to log new exercises.</p>
    </section>
    <section class="section-lvl1">
      <h2>Logging a New Exercise</h2>
      <p><a href="/api/exercise/new" target="_self">Add an exercise</a> using the unique user ID you created.</p>
    </section>
    <section class="section-lvl1">
      <h2>Retrieving a List of Users</h2>
      <p>To get the list of all the registered users, go to the route:</p>
      <pre>
        <code class="api-link">https://autumnchris-exercise-tracker-api.onrender.com/api/users</code>
        <button type="button" class="button copy-button api-users" title="Copy to clipboard" aria-label="copy to clipboard"><span class="copy-icon fa-regular fa-copy"></span></button>
      </pre>
    </section>
    <section class="section-lvl1">
      <h2>Retrieving Exercise Data for a User</h2>
      <p>To get data for a specific user, go to the route below, replacing <code>&lt;your-user-id&gt;</code> with your user ID:</p>
      <pre>
        <code class="api-link">https://autumnchris-exercise-tracker-api.onrender.com/api/user/log/&lt;your-user-id&gt;</code>
        <button type="button" class="button copy-button api-user-log" title="Copy to clipboard" aria-label="copy to clipboard"><span class="copy-icon fa-regular fa-copy"></span></button>
      </pre>
      <p>You can also filter the list of exercise logs that get returned. One method involves limiting the number of logs, such as:</p>
      <pre>
        <code class="api-link">https://autumnchris-exercise-tracker-api.onrender.com/api/user/log/&lt;your-user-id&gt;?limit=&lt;number-of-logs&gt;</code>
        <button type="button" class="button copy-button api-user-log-limit" title="Copy to clipboard" aria-label="copy to clipboard"><span class="copy-icon fa-regular fa-copy"></span></button>
      </pre>
      <p>You can also filter logs that occur within a specific set of dates written in <code>YYYY-MM-DD</code> formatting, such as:</p>
      <pre>
        <code class="api-link">https://autumnchris-exercise-tracker-api.onrender.com/api/user/log/&lt;your-user-id&gt;?from=&lt;earliest-date&gt;&to=&lt;latest-date&gt;</code>
        <button type="button" class="button copy-button api-user-log-dates" title="Copy to clipboard" aria-label="copy to clipboard"><span class="copy-icon fa-regular fa-copy"></span></button>
      </pre>
      <p>You can also both limit the number of logs as well as select the date range, such as:</p>
      <pre>
        <code class="api-link">https://autumnchris-exercise-tracker-api.onrender.com/api/user/log/&lt;your-user-id&gt;?from=&lt;earliest-date&gt;&to=&lt;latest-date&gt;&limit=&lt;number-of-logs&gt;</code>
        <button type="button" class="button copy-button api-user-log-limit-and-dates" title="Copy to clipboard" aria-label="copy to clipboard"><span class="copy-icon fa-regular fa-copy"></span></button>
      </pre>
    </section>
  </article>
</main>
